  "texts": [
    "Training involves multiple pass through the training data to achieve convergence.",
    "The term convergence in the context of machine learning is the point at which the prediction error or loss is within some predetermined value range where further training no longer improves the model.",
    "The point of convergence is equally applicable to self-supervised and supervised types of machine learning.",
    "Perplexity is another measure often used to determine when the machine has learned sufficiently well to generalize on unseen data.",
    "The goal is to minimize perplexity, which indicates that the model consistently assigns higher probabilities to the correct predictions."
  ],
